menu "pixfrog LED output"

    choice PIXFROG_LED_OUTPUT_BACKEND
        prompt "LED bus output backend"
        default PIXFROG_LED_OUTPUT_LCD_CAM
        help
            Peripheral driving the 16-bit LED bus. Both backends implement
            the same pixfrog::lcd:: interface and emit identical sample
            streams; they differ in the engine moving the bytes.

        config PIXFROG_LED_OUTPUT_LCD_CAM
            bool "LCD_CAM RGB panel"
            help
                esp_lcd RGB panel in refresh_on_demand mode. Frames are split
                into v_res lines of <=4092 samples (12-bit timing registers);
                a 3-PCLK blank separates lines, absorbed between NRZ bits.

        config PIXFROG_LED_OUTPUT_PARLIO
            bool "PARLIO TX (loop transmission)"
            help
                PARLIO TX unit in loop transmission mode: the frame is a flat
                DMA buffer repeated back-to-back (the encoded reset tail
                separates repeats), no line-geometry registers involved.
                Buffer swaps happen gapless at frame boundaries.

    endchoice

endmenu
